on)" class="mw-redirect">Geber</a>.</div>
<!--  He was known as the father of chemistry. The consensus in the talk page supported by references is to mention both the Persian and Arabic ethnicities, please do not change. This was a cause of edit wars -->
<table class="infobox biography vcard" style="width:22em" about="#mwt3" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Infobox religious biography\n","href":"./Template:Infobox_religious_biography"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"\n"},"era":{"wt":"[[Islamic Golden Age]]"},"image":{"wt":"Jabir ibn Hayyan.jpg"},"caption":{"wt":"15th-century European portrait of \"Geber\", Codici Ashburnhamiani 1166, Biblioteca Medicea Laurenziana, Florence"},"name":{"wt":"Jabir ibn Hayyan"},"title":{"wt":"Father of Chemistry"},"religion":{"wt":"[[Islam]]"},"birth_name":{"wt":"Abu Musa Jabir ibn Hayyan"},"birth_date":{"wt":"c. 721 CE &lt;br />[[Tus, Iran|Tus]], [[Greater Khurasan|Khurasan]], [[Umayyad Caliphate]]&lt;ref>&apos;&apos;Tus&apos;&apos;, V. Minorsky, &apos;&apos;&apos;The Encyclopaedia of Islam&apos;&apos;&apos;, Vol. X, ed. P.J. Bearman, T. Bianquis, C.E. Bosworth, E. van Donzel and W.P. Heinrichs, (Brill, 2000), 741.&lt;/ref>"},"death_date":{"wt":"c. 815 CE"},"death_place":{"wt":"[[Kufa]]"},"region":{"wt":""},"main_interests":{"wt":"&lt;small>[[Alchemy and chemistry in medieval Islam|Alchemy and Chemistry]], [[astronomy in medieval Islam|Astronomy]], [[astrology in medieval Islam|Astrology]], [[Medicine in the medieval Islamic world|Medicine and Pharmacy]], [[Islamic philosophy|Philosophy]], [[physics in medieval Islam|Physics]], philanthropist&lt;/small>"},"notable_ideas":{"wt":""},"works":{"wt":"&lt;small>&apos;&apos;[[Kitab al-Kimya]]&apos;&apos;, &apos;&apos;[[Kitab al-Sab&apos;een]]&apos;&apos;, &apos;&apos;[[Book of the Kingdom]]&apos;&apos;, &apos;&apos;[[Book of the Balances]]&apos;&apos;, &apos;&apos;[[Book of Eastern Mercury]]&apos;&apos;, etc.&lt;/small>"},"influences":{"wt":"[[Ja&apos;far al-Sadiq]], [[Alchemy]], [[Harbi al-Himyari]]"},"influenced":{"wt":"[[Dhul-Nun al-Misri]], [[Al-Kindi]], [[Alchemy]], [[Chemistry]]"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAw"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background:
