A68&amp;dq=jabir+hayyan+Sabian#v=onepage&amp;q=jabir%20kinsmen&amp;f=false" id="mwAiM"><i id="mwAiQ">Alchemy</i></a>. Courier Corporation. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwAiU">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAiY"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-486-15114-4" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-486-15114-4" id="mwAic">978-0-486-15114-4</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Alchemy&amp;rft.pub=Courier+Corporation&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-486-15114-4&amp;rft.aulast=Holmyard&amp;rft.aufirst=E.J.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2F%3Fid%3DvHz7VQz-ucgC%26pg%3DPA68%26dq%3Djabir%2Bhayyan%2BSabian%23v%3Donepage%26q%3Djabir%2520kinsmen%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJabir+ibn+Hayyan" class="Z3988" about="#mwt63" id="mwAig"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt63" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAik"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-Haq_1994_14–20-27" id="cite_note-Haq_1994_14–20-27"><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-Haq_1994_14–20_27-0" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Haq_1994_14–20-27" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt95" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last":{"wt":"Haq"},"first":{"wt":"Syed N."},"editor":{"wt":""},"title":{"wt":"Names, Natures and Things"},"url":{"wt":""},"edition":{"wt":""},"year":{"wt":"1994"},"publisher":{"wt":"Boston Studies in the Philosophy of Science, Volume 158/ Kluwar Academic Publishers"},"location":{"wt":"Dordrecht, The Netherlands"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-7923-3254-1"},"pages":{"wt":"14–20"},"quote":{"wt":""}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAio">Haq, Syed N. (1994). <i id="mwAis">Names, Natures and Things</i>. Dordrecht, The Netherlands: Boston Studies in the Philosophy of Science, Volume 158/ Kluwar Academic Publishers. pp.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAiw"> </span>14–20. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwAi0">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAi4"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-7923-3254-1" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-7923-3254-1" id="mwAi8">978-0-7923-3254-1</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Names%2C+Natures+and+Things&amp;rft.place=Dordrecht%2C+The+Netherlands&amp;rft.pages=14-20&amp;rft.pub=Boston+Studies+in+the+Philosophy+of+Science%2C+Volume+158%2F+Kluwar+Academic+Publishers&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-7923-3254-1&amp;rft.aulast=Haq&amp;rft.aufirst=Syed+N.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJabir+ibn+Hayyan" class="Z3988" about="#mwt95" id="mwAjA"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt95" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAjE"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-Iranica_jafar-28" id="cite_note-Iranica_jafar-28"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-Iranica_jafar_28-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-Iranica_jafar_28-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Iranica_jafar-28" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt96" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/jafar-al-sadeq-iv-and-esoteric-sciences"},"title":{"wt":"Iranica &apos;&apos;JAʿFAR AL-ṢĀDEQ iv. And Esoteric sciences&apos;&apos;"},"accessdate":{"wt":"11 June 2011"},"quote":{"wt":"The historical relations between Jaʿfar al-Ṣādeq and Jāber b. Ḥayyān remain very controversial, as they are linked to still unresolved questions about dating, composition, and authorship of the texts attributed to Jāber. Scholars such as Julius Ruska, Paul Kraus, and [[Pierre Lory]] consider Jaʿfar al-Ṣādeq’s involvement in the transmission of alchemical knowledge as a literary fiction, whereas Fuat Sezgin, Toufic Fahd, and Nomanul Haq are rather inclined to accept the existence of alchemical activity in Medina in Jaʿfar al-Ṣādeq’s time, although they remain cautious regarding the authenticity of the attribution of the Jaberian corpus to Jāber b. Ḥayyān and of the alchemical works to Jaʿfar al-Ṣādeq (Ruska, 1924, pp. 40–52; idem, 1927, pp. 264–266; Kraus, I, pp. lv-lvii; Lory, pp. 14–21, 57–59, 101–107; Sezgin, I, p. 529, IV, pp. 128–311; Fahd, 1970, pp. 139–141; Nomanul Haq, pp. 3–47)."}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAjI"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/jafar-al-sadeq-iv-and-esoteric-sciences" id="mwAjM">"Iranica <i id="mwAjQ">JAʿFAR AL-ṢĀDEQ iv. And Esoteric sciences</i>"</a><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwAjU">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwAjY">11 June</span> 2011</span>. <q id="mwAjc">The historical relations between Jaʿfar al-Ṣādeq and Jāber b. Ḥayyān remain very controversial, as they are linked to still unresolved questions about dating, composition, and authorship of the texts attributed to Jāber. Scholars such as Julius Ruska, Paul Kraus, and <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Pierre_Lory" title="Pierre Lory" id="mwAjg">Pierre Lory</a> consider Jaʿfar al-Ṣādeq’s involvement in the transmission of alchemical knowledge as a literary fiction, whereas Fuat Sezgin, Toufic Fahd, and Nomanul Haq are rather inclined to accept the existence of alchemical activity in Medina in Jaʿfar al-Ṣādeq’s time, although they remain cautious regarding the authenticity of the attribution of the Jaberian corpus to Jāber b. Ḥayyān and of the alchemical works to Jaʿfar al-Ṣādeq (Ruska, 1924, pp. 40–52; idem, 1927, pp. 264–266; Kraus, I, pp. lv-lvii; Lory, pp. 14–21, 57–59, 101–107; Sezgin, I, p. 529, IV, pp. 128–311; Fahd, 1970, pp. 139–141; Nomanul Haq, pp. 3–47).</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Iranica+JA%CA%BFFAR+AL-%E1%B9%A2%C4%80DEQ+iv.+And+Esoteric+sciences&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iranicaonline.org%2Farticles%2Fjafar-al-sadeq-iv-and-esoteric-sciences&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJabir+ibn+Hayyan" class="Z3988" about="#mwt96" id="mwAjk"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt96" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAjo"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-29" id="cite_note-29"><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-29" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-29" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt104" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Cite book","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"title":{"wt":"Medieval Islamic Civilization"},"author1":{"wt":"[[Josef W. Meri]]"},"author2":{"wt":"[[Jere L. Bacharach]]"},"publisher":{"wt":"Taylor and Francis"},"year":{"wt":"2006"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-415-96691-7"},"page":{"wt":"25"},"postscript":{"wt":"&lt;!--None-->"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAjs"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Josef_W._Meri" title="Josef W. Meri" id="mwAjw">Josef W. Meri</a>; <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Jere_L._Bacharach" title="Jere L. Bacharach" id="mwAj0">Jere L. Bacharach</a> (2006). <i id="mwAj4">Medieval Islamic Civilization</i>. Taylor and Francis. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAj8"> </span>25. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwAkA">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwAkE"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-415-96691-7" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-415-96691-7" id="mwAkI">978-0-415-96691-7</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Medieval+Islamic+Civilization&amp;rft.pages=25&amp;rft.pub=Taylor+and+Francis&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-415-96691-7&amp;rft.au=Josef+W.+Meri&amp;rft.au=Jere+L.+Bacharach&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJabir+ibn+Hayyan" class="Z3988" about="#mwt104" id="mwAkM"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt104" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAkQ"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-30" id="cite_note-30"><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-30" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-30" class="mw-reference-text">Jabir Ibn Hayyan. Vol. 1. Le corpus des ecrits jabiriens. George Olms Verlag, 1989</span></li><li about="#cite_note-31" id="cite_note-31"><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-31" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-31" class="mw-reference-text">Paul Kraus, <i id="mwAkU">Jabir ibn Hayyan: Contribution à l'histoire des idées scientifiques dans l'Islam</i>, cited Robert Irwin, 'The long siesta' in <i id="mwAkY"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Times_Literary_Supplement" title="Times Literary Supplement" id="mwAkc" class="mw-redirect">Times Literary Supplement</a></i>, 25/1/2008 p.8</span></li><li about="#cite_note-32" id="cite_note-32"><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-32" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-32" class="mw-reference-text">Syed Nomanul Haq, <i id="mwAkg">Names, Natures and Things: The Alchemist Jābir ibn Hayyān and his Kitāb al-Ahjār (Book of Stones)</i>, Springer Science &amp; Business Media (2012), pp. 11–12</span></li><li about="#cite_note-33" id="cite_note-33"><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-33" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-33" class="mw-reference-text">Julian, Franklyn, <i id="mwAkk">Dictionary of the Occult</i>, Kessinger Publishing, 2003, <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt120" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"ISBN","href":"./Template:ISBN"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"0-7661-2816-4"},"2":{"wt":"978-0-7661-2816-3"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAko"/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" about="#mwt120" id="mwAks">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" about="#mwt120" id="mwAkw"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/0-7661-2816-4" title="Special:BookSources/0-7661-2816-4" about="#mwt120" id="mwAk0">0-7661-2816-4</a><span about="#mwt120" id="mwAk4">, </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-7661-2816-3" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-7661-2816-3" about="#mwt120" id="mwAk8">978-0-7661-2816-3</a>, p. 9.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-KIMIĀ_Alchemy-34" id="cite_note-KIMIĀ_Alchemy-34"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-KIMIĀ_Alchemy_34-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-KIMIĀ_Alchemy_34-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-