ia+Britannica+Eleventh+Edition&amp;rft.pages=545-546&amp;rft.edition=11th&amp;rft.date=1910&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJabir+ibn+Hayyan" class="Z3988" about="#mwt236" id="mwAww"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt236" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAw0"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-66" id="cite_note-66"><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-66" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-66" class="mw-reference-text">An authoritative summary and analysis of current scholarship on this question may be found in Lawrence M. Principe, <i id="mwAw4">The Secrets of Alchemy</i>, University of Chicago Press, 2013, pp. 33–45 and 54–58.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-hassan-67" id="cite_note-hassan-67"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-hassan_67-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Jabir_ibn_Hayyan#cite_ref-hassan_67-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-hassan-67" class="mw-reference-text">Ahmad Y. al-Hassan, <i id="mwAw8">Critical-Issues Studies in al-Kimya′: Critical Issues in Latin and Arabic Alchemy and Chemistry</i>, published as book by <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=IMc8cgAACAAJ&amp;dq=Critical-Issues+Studies+in+al-Kimya&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ei=imODU4qpG4aS7Qa_x4GwCQ&amp;ved=0CDEQ6AEwAA" id="mwAxA">Olms in 2009</a> and as article by <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1600-0498.2010.00206.x/abstract" id="mwAxE">Centaurus journal in 2011</a>. Online versions are available at <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.history-science-technology.com/geber/geber.html" id="mwAxI"><i